				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2020 03:31:04 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Dester52</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6292616</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I love the overall article. My only nitpick is the little line on the Blood-type being &quot;all&quot;. Inherently, these different blood types would cause adverse reactions to any &quot;parts&quot; of the organism having differing native blood types. Maybe a line calling out this particular anomalous effect, or, perhaps more fitting, a line on the damage this is causing adding to the short-lived nature of this skip, as well as fitting in with the overall fully real functioning of this anomaly.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
